quran[15]{c,v,t}:
  20,90,"Yet Aaron had aforetime said to them, 'My people, you have been tempted by this thing, no more; surety your Lord is the All-merciful; therefore follow me, and obey my commandment"
  20,91,"We will not cease,' they said, 'to cleave to it, until Moses returns to us"
  20,92,"Moses said, 'What prevented thee, Aaron, when thou sawest them in error"
  20,93,so that thou didst not follow after me? Didst thou then disobey my commandment
  20,94,"Son of my mother,' Aaron said, 'take me not by the beard, or the head! I was fearful that thou wouldst say, \"Thou hast divided the Children of Israel, and thou hast not observed my word"
  20,95,"Moses said, 'And thou, Samaritan, what was thy business"
  20,96,"I beheld what they beheld not,' he said, 'and I seized a handful of dust from the messenger's track, and cast it into the thing. So my soul prompted me"
  20,97,"Depart!' said Moses. 'It shall be thine all this life to cry \"Untouchable!\" And thereafter a tryst awaits thee thou canst not fail to keep Behold thy god, to whom all the day thou wast cleaving! We will surely burn it and scatter its ashes into the sea"
  20,98,"Your God is only the One God; there is no god, but He alone who in His knowledge embraces everything"
  20,99,"So We relate to thee stories of what has gone before, and We have given thee a remembrance from Us"
  20,100,"Whosoever turns away from it, upon the Day of Resurrection He shall bear a fardel"
  20,101,therein abiding forever; how evil upon the Day of Resurrection that burden for them
  20,102,On the day the Trumpet is blown; and We shall muster the sinners upon that day with eyes staring
  20,103,"whispering one to another, 'You have tarried only ten nights"
  20,104,"We know very well what they will say, when the justest of them in the way will say, 'You have tarried only a day"